{
  "children": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Turing Machine"
        }
      ],
      "level": 1,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "A "
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Turing machine"
            }
          ],
          "type": "bold"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " is a mathematical model of computation describing an abstract machine"
        },
        {
          "label": "turing1936",
          "type": "footnote_ref"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ". It manipulates symbols on a strip of tape according to a table of rules."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "max_level": 4,
      "min_level": 2,
      "type": "toc"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "History"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The concept was introduced by "
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Alan Turing"
            }
          ],
          "type": "italic"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " in 1936 in his paper \"On Computable Numbers\""
        },
        {
          "label": "turing1936",
          "type": "footnote_ref"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ". The machine was designed to formalize the concept of an algorithm."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Despite its simplicity, a Turing machine can simulate any computer algorithm, no matter how complex. This is the basis of the "
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Church-Turing thesis"
            }
          ],
          "type": "bold"
        },
        {
          "label": "church",
          "type": "footnote_ref"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Formal Definition"
        }
      ],
      "id": "formal-def",
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "A Turing machine is a 7-tuple "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "M = (Q, \\Sigma, \\Gamma, \\delta, q_0, q_{accept}, q_{reject})"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " where:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "items": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "Q"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " is a finite set of states"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "\\Sigma"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " is the input alphabet"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "\\Gamma"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " is the tape alphabet"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "\\delta"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " is the transition function"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "q_0"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " is the start state"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "q_{accept}"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " is the accept state"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "inline_math",
                  "value": "q_{reject}"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": " is the reject state"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "unordered_list"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Variants"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Multi-tape Turing Machine"
        }
      ],
      "level": 3,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "A multi-tape machine uses "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "k"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " tapes, each with its own head. It has been proven that any multi-tape machine can be simulated by a single-tape machine."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Non-deterministic Turing Machine"
        }
      ],
      "level": 3,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "A non-deterministic Turing machine (NDTM) can have multiple possible transitions for a given state-symbol pair."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Significance"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
